          <msContents>
            <summary>Text for private consultation to be employed in rites and prayers performed during the month of Kārtika (October/November). Rites including bathing, fasting, fire, and other kinds of offerings, as well as numerous mantras that need to be performed during the month Kārtika, which is especially auspicious for the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa. Manuscript contains mythology related to this figure.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kārtikamāhātmya</title>
              <title type="vernacular">कार्तिकमाहात्म्य</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Maisūrakara, Viśvanātha Śāstri</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīsanatkumārasaṃhitāyāṃ kārtikamāhātmye sūryāruṇasaṃvāde vratodyāpanavidhikathanaṃ nāmacaturviṃśodhyāyaḥ // śrīviśveśvarpaṇam astu // śrīrādhādāmodarārpaṇam astu // idaṃ maisūrakaropanāmakaviśvanāthaśāstriṇā likhitam asti // saṃvat 1941 pauṣavadya 2 gurau // śrīsarveṣāṃ śubhaṃ bhūyāt // (f. 42v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
